category: GLAD-JECTIVES
category comment: 

clue: "'Twas the Night Before Christmas" described St. Nicholas as "a right" this "old elf"

response: jolly

clue: This 7-letter adjective can mean happy or able to float on liquid

response: buoyant

clue: This cheery adjective literally means "pertaining to Jupiter"

response: jovial

clue: Add "-ation" to the end of this adjective meaning happy & you get a stage of canonization

response: beatific

clue: "Humor" us & tell us of this happy word whose name derives from the Latin for "blood"

response: sanguine

